Flower.create(name: "Alstroemeria", season:"Summer", color:"Shades of red, orange, purple, green, white, flecked and striped", price: 7, quantity: 8, image_url: "https://www.gardenia.net/storage/app/public/plant_family/detail/18488792_mOptimized.jpg", description: "These are more often called either Peruvian Lilies or Lilies of the Incas and are native to South America. Peruvian Lilies come in a variety of warm colors like pink and orange and are symbolic of friendship, wealth and devotion. These flowers bloom in late spring/early summer when exposed to direct sunlight and watered weekly (water more often when you notice soil looking dry, water less when the soil looks soggy).", store_id: s1.id)


Flower.create(name: "Black-Eyed Susan", season:"March to May", color:"Bright yellow", price: 7, quantity: 8, image_url: "https://jmoreliving.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/blackeyedsusan.jpg", description: "Cheerful black-eyed Susans are one of North America‚Äôs favorite perennial wildflowers that are frequently seen in fields and meadows. They are a popular addition to a sunny garden since they are hardy, they can tolerate drought and a variety of soils, and they can reseed and come back year after year. Black-eyed Susans are perfect for a beginner gardener. Their jolly orange petals and brown centers represent encouragement and can be given to a friend who could use a bouquet of optimism.", store_id: s1.id)


