Flower.create(name: "Petunia", season:"Summer", color:"Pink, purple, red, and white", price: 7, quantity: 8, image_url: "https://www.indiaplants.com/photos/Plants/P/img1459_33573547.jpg", description: "The cheerful petunia, a staple of old-fashioned gardens, planters, and hanging pots, is more vivid than ever with red, yellow, pink, purple, lavender, white, multicolored, or striped blossoms. They are reliable flowers that will bloom from spring through autumn if grown in the sun and deadheaded consistently. Many of them feel sticky to the touch due to sap that is exuded from the plant tissues to protect them from insect pests. Petunias are native to South America and are related to tomatoes, peppers, eggplants, and tobacco.", store_id: s1.id)

Flower.create(name: "Ranunculus", season:"Early spring until the beginning of summer", color:"White, pink, orange, red, yellow, purple, and cream in various shades", price: 7, quantity: 8, image_url: "https://images.tulipworld.com/mmTW/Images/450X450/3374.jpg", description: "Ranunculus flowers are varieties of the big, showy, Persian buttercups that grow from claw-shaped corms and come in a variety of bright colors. Their layers of paper-thin, glossy petals give the blossoms a rose-like appearance that is appealing for wedding bouquets or  long-lasting cut flowers. Ranunculus are not commonly grown in home gardens, but they could be. Southern gardeners can plant the corms in the fall for spring blooms, and northern gardeners can plant in the early spring for summer blossoms.", store_id: s1.id)

Flower.create(name: "Roses", season:"Midspring to fall", color:"Red, yellow, pink, purple, orange, and white", price: 7, quantity: 8, image_url: "https://www.sallyhelmy.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/header-2.jpg", description: "Like the flower itself, the history of the rose is very colorful. Roses have been naturally growing for over 35 million years! However, they were not known to be cultivated until about 5,000 years ago. Their usage began not just as a decorative touch to one‚Äôs home, but they were also used for medicinal purposes, to make perfumes, and their petals were even used as confetti for festive occasions. Getting your roses into water quickly is the first step in caring for them. Fill a vase ¬æ full of fresh, cool tap water. The roses will absorb the water, soaking up the nutrients that will travel up to the bloom and create a lively flower. Check the water level in your rose‚Äôs vase every day and add more water as needed. Shop these classic flowers for Valentine‚Äôs Day!", store_id: s1.id)

Flower.create(name: "Snapdragon", season:"Spring and fall", color:"Pink, orange, yellow, peach, purple, white, red and bicolor.", price: 7, quantity: 8, image_url: "https://h2.commercev3.net/cdn.gurneys.com/images/800/69576.jpg", description: "Snapdragon flowers, shaped like little dragon snouts, are native to the United States, North Africa, and Europe, and have been widespread posies for centuries. Their flowers bloom from the bottom to the top of tall stalks in the summer and fall and come in yellow, peach, pink, orange, purple, red, white, and bicolor. Snapdragons are picky about their pollinators! Large bumblebees are the only insects that are strong enough to open the upper and lower lips of the snapdragon flower to crawl inside to drink the nectar and inadvertently cover themselves in pollen.", store_id: s1.id)

Flower.create(name: "Sunflowers", season:"Summer into autumn", color:"Yellow", price: 7, quantity: 8, image_url: "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/81MR7K2D+XS._AC_SX466_.jpg", description: "Sunflowers are one of the most popular flower types and are best known for their dazzling yellow color and large size. Sunflowers generally symbolize adoration, loyalty and longevity in the language of flowers. Native Americans view sunflowers as a symbol of harvest and bounty since the flower provides seeds and pigments on top of being visually beautiful. Sunflowers need direct sunlight for 6 to 8 hours per day and require hot conditions to flower well. Sunflowers also have long roots that require plenty of room to spread out, so soil should be well dug and not too dense for growth. Avoid over fertilization or risk your stems breaking in the fall.", store_id: s1.id)

Flower.create(name: "Tulips", season:"Spring", color:"Purple, pink, red, orange, and yellow", price: 7, quantity: 8, image_url: "https://www.gardeningknowhow.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/07/tulips.jpg", description: "There are over 150 species of tulips with over 3,000 different varieties and are part of the lily family. Like most common flowers, tulips come in a large variety of colors that each have their own meaning. As a signal of the arrival of spring, these blooms are often associated with the Easter holiday. Tulips were at one point more valuable than gold in Holland during a period of ‚ÄúTulip Mania‚Äù and their popularity has only spread with time! Tulip bulbs should be planted in the fall in areas where they can receive partial to full sun. Tulips will fare better in soil that allows for drainage since over watering will drown the bulb and roots.", store_id: s1.id)


Flower.create(name: "Violet", season:"Late winter and early spring", color:"Purple/violet", price: 7, quantity: 8, image_url: "https://www.bluestoneperennials.com/img/PHVP/650/PHVP-0-Phlox-subulata-Violet-Pinwheels-wg.1574190019.jpg", description: "There are over 500 species of these merry little wildflowers mostly in the temperate northern hemisphere, popping up in lawns, woodlands, streambanks, and hillsides. True violets are annual, perennial, or even small shrubs with white, yellow, lavender, or purple flowers. Our garden pansies are also violets but are larger, multicolored cultivars of the European flower known as heartsease. The violet is February‚Äôs birth flower, and the state flower of Illinois, New Jersey, and Wisconsin.", store_id: s1.id)

Flower.create(name: "Zinnia", season:"Late spring until the first frost in fall", color:"Pink, purple, yellow, orange, lavender, white, red, and green", price: 7, quantity: 8, image_url: "https://www.gardendesign.com/pictures/images/900x705Max/dream-team-s-portland-garden_6/zinnia-flowers-mixed-flowers-shutterstock-com_12811.jpg", description: "Colorful, easy-to-grow zinnias are a beginner gardener‚Äôs dream. They can be seeded from the last frost to early summer and will consistently produce blooms all season if dying blooms are deadheaded ‚Äî truly a ‚Äúcut and come again‚Äù flower. They are herbaceous annuals, native to Mexico, South America, and the southwestern U.S. that are of varying heights, with bright 1‚Äù to 7‚Äù diameter flowers that are single, semi-double, or double. Zinnias are perfect for a butterfly garden, with their red, pink, purple, yellow, white, or orange blossoms that attract pollinators of all kinds including hummingbirds.", store_id: s1.id)

Flower.create(name: "Ageratum", season:"Late spring through fall", color:"Blue, purple, white, and pink", price: 7, quantity: 8, image_url: "https://www.gardendesign.com/pictures/images/900x850Max/site_3/blue-mink-floss-flower-ageratum-houstonianum-shutterstock-com_13700.jpg", description: "Ageratums are also known as the floss flower. These plants produce flowers that are fluffy and last for an extended period of time.Most types are mounding plants six to ten inches tall and wide, but there are taller types.The common garden ageratum (A. houstonianum), also known as floss flower and blue mink, is frequently cultivated as an ornamental annual. Several dwarf varieties are commonly used as edging plants.", store_id: s1.id)

